he creation of a vibrant cultural destination in the Cultural District of Saadiyat Island.\n\nGehry created clusters of galleries connected by catwalks that center on a common courtyard, and additional vertical clusters of galleries that allow for a variety of vertical and horizontal exhibition spaces, providing unprecedented curatorial flexibility. Monumentally scaled cones provide natural cooling and ventilation of the courtyards in a  nod to traditional Middle Eastern wind towers.\n\nL’Observatoire scope includes the façade and site lighting as well as interior public spaces including lobbies, exhibition spaces, auditorium, cafés, restaurants and shops."},"team":[{"name":"Alex Miller","slug":"alex-miller","primaryOffice":"No Longer Employed","id":"40e17d25-0341-5b0e-a1d7-31f5b076b552"},{"name":"Gianni Franceschi","slug":"gianni-franceschi","primaryOffice":"New York","id":"f9d3ee99-d08d-574c-8e6c-601b042edde8"},{"name":"Glenn Fujimura","slug":"glenn-fujimura","primaryOffice":"No Longer Employed","id":"86347cf1-f143-5b84-9370-ab56dc28e1bc"},{"name":"Leah Xandora","slug":"leah-xandora","primaryOffice":"New York","id":"a23c520d-b7f7-5ebb-abb8-76dd1f2c48c0"},{"name":"Wen Y. Lin","slug":"wen-y-lin","primaryOffice":"New York","id":"f3faefaa-d613-5f53-be55-286b88f3eb68"},{"name":"Papon Kasettratat","slug":"papon-kasettratat","primaryOffice":"New York","id":"75c19578-0d40-572f-8997-505bf3a3359b"}],"press":null,"photoCredit":null,"projectLeader":[{"name":"Wei Jien","slug":"wei-jien","primaryOffice":"New York","id":"cdf1630a-c99b-52be-a052-1d801938caee"}],"metadata":{"tags":[]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"guggenheim-abu-dhabi"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1395536887","143701507"],"slicesMap":{}}